26:09.701 --> 26:14.729
That's true. But we cannot attempt to
understand the world by intellect alone.

26:15.407 --> 26:17.136
-Carl Jung.
-Yes.

26:17.810 --> 26:20.870
From his treatise <i>Psychological Types.</i>

26:20.979 --> 26:24.380
-So...
-Jung, the New Agers' favourite psychologist.

26:24.483 --> 26:26.747
Because he wasn't
afraid to bring God into the equation.

26:26.819 --> 26:28.116
Well, he wasn't afraid to bring God into...

26:28.220 --> 26:31.621
-Clay, Clay, come on.
-Let's do it. I know. Come on. Let's start.

26:31.723 --> 26:33.486
-Shall we?
-I'm ready.

26:34.126 --> 26:35.252
Very well. Please, give me your hand.

26:35.327 --> 26:36.988
Okay.

26:37.496 --> 26:39.225
This way. Okay.

26:46.004 --> 26:47.494
You work with money.

26:48.841 --> 26:49.899
That's right.

26:51.243 --> 26:53.609
And you've recently lost something.

26:55.781 --> 27:01.242
-No, I don't think so.
-No. No, you haven't lost anything.

27:02.354 --> 27:04.686
But something's been taken from you.

27:05.591 --> 27:06.751
No.

27:07.359 --> 27:10.294
-RHAM JAS: A button.
-Oh, my God. Yes!

27:11.196 --> 27:13.027
Well, anyone can see
she's missing a button! So what?

27:13.132 --> 27:14.360
But, Clay, it was really strange.

27:14.466 --> 27:16.866
The old woman today,
she took a button from my sleeve.

27:16.969 --> 27:20.803
-Why would she do that?
-If you would both please just be quiet!

27:50.736 --> 27:51.725
(GASPS)

28:20.265 --> 28:21.425
(SCREECHING)

28:33.445 --> 28:36.608
-I think that's enough for tonight.
-What's wrong?

28:36.715 --> 28:42.244
I'm tired, and I see it's become quite late.
I will, of course, refund your money.

28:42.354 --> 28:44.879
Wait, wait, wait! Did you see something?

28:46.458 --> 28:48.085
